I was with a party of 11 the night of the annual Christmas parade. We were seated at an excellent location and for a group our size were not crowded at all. The service was outstanding from the moment we arrived until we left. Everyone loved the food, from the calamari and other assorted appetizers to our main courses. The pastas were fantastic and my filet was one of the best I've ever eaten. My 10 oz filet was only $35...at nearly every other steakhouse in Chicago, it would have been $55-60. Probably the worst restaurant meal I ever had! Waiters are rude and my meal was so spicy that my nose was running! The restaurant is nice and the hostess at the door was very nice. The problems started when we received our plates. We were a party of three and two of us ordered the scallops. They where covered in chilli oil in a way that only a fool would do to such a delicate tasting seafood plate. We both were crying, our noses were running, it was horrible; we could only taste pepper. I was wondering if someone was playing a trick on us. For a 40$ plate, it is unacceptable to have that level of amateurism. When the waiter finally asked us how was everything, after 15 minutes and our plates were finished, I mentioned politely that the scallops were very spicy, almost inedible. He didn’t say a word and, very unapologetically, went to get the menu and pointed at the words “chilli oil” in the ingredients list of my meal. I acknowledged but mentioned that the quantity of oil was completely disproportional. I received no excuses, no sympathy and nobody suggested a new meal or to redo the meal, despite the fact that it’s a 40$ plate. The service level of that restaurant is atrociously bad. There are so many other good restaurants in Chicago, forget about that one!

I was really excited to try somewhere new but was very unimpressed. We went for a date night last Saturday night around 5 pm.  We were going to an Opera after so we had an earlier dinner. Starters: French Martini was made well. Appetizer: Scallops over pork belly and sweet potatoes was good. But was missing seasoning. Especially salt. Calamari appetizer came with fried salmon and shrimp as well. This had to have been the most chewy hard to eat Calamari I have ever had.  I hated it.  The salmon tasted so fishy that I was stuck with a greasy fishy after taste and had to order another drink so I can swish it around to try to get the flavor out. Next course, I had the special New York steak with garlic mashed and asparagus.  Thank God it was charred and I asked for it medium.  Otherwise there would be no flavor and it would of been completely raw.  As it was already purple almost and cold in the middle.  The Garlic mashed was my very favorite part of the dish.  I only ate part of it because my husband couldn’t eat all of his and needed mine. My husbands dish was the mixed seafood in a Tomatoe garlic sauce. The lobster was very over cooked to the point it was curled up and very hard to chew.  As was the mussels and clams in the dish. Everything was tough.  I am not sure who was cooking that night but everything tasted like it was flash fried.  Possibly cooked the night before than microwaved as the food was ordered.  I honestly have had better cooking by my 14 year old.  I will never go back here.  A huge waste of money and a date night. I am shocked they have any good reviews. I hope they read this and start seasoning their food and making sure they don’t over cook their seafood and undercook their meat.

We ate here on new year's eve, we had the new year's eve 4  course dinner for $75 each person at 8pm. I am sorry to say, my husband and I were not impressed. I had the shrimp cocktail for the antipasti, the shrimp tasted like previously frozen from any grocery store and the salad it came with was sub-par.  Our waitress actually did not even come to our table until we spent 20 minutes starring at our menus.The waitress apologized for us waiting and said there was a mess up in tables she was serving.  Long story short, the servers kept bringing us incorrect food plates... Instead of our main he brought dessert. And then wasn't provided with cutlery for our main, and had to wait for that too.  Waitress brought our drinks to the wrong table.  At the end, when the waitress brought our check, she said to us, ready for the damage?  At the end...the waitress didn't wish us anything, I wished the waitress a happy new year.  I rarely write reviews but this was supposed to by my new year's eve dinner, and you guys really dampened it. Also at $75 per person, truly the service and food should be impeccable for a memorable experience...i felt this fell short.  We had  Christmas dinner at Luke in New Orleans 2017, and spent half as much there, and honestly I loved it there. The waiters there were so attentive and the experience was lovely, food was truly fresh and hot on the plate.  We will not visit 312 again.

Do get the Linguine Nere - it's spicy, it's rich but in a small enough portion that you don't feel overfed, it's tangy, it's damned satisfying  Drinks were okay for being in the city - I've had worse and better  Service was decent for the circumstances - there was a private event that took up half the upstairs space and a majority of the waitstaff and it was busy otherwise, so we waited for about 20 minutes for someone to come take our order. They did take the lasagna off our bill when we expressed our displeasure without hesitation and everyone was nice.  Atmosphere was typical of a downtown restaurant - a bit cramped with small tables, though the seats were nice.  All in all I'd return - no lasagna next time tho.
